Package pandemicGame

Class Virus

java.lang.Object
pandemicGame.OnscreenObject
pandemicGame.Virus
All Implemented Interfaces:
AnimatedObject
public class Virus
extends OnscreenObject
implements AnimatedObject
This class creates the virus class with methods to allow it to move, split, change point values and wrap around the screen properly

    • Virus

    • Virus

      public Virus​(AbstractAnimation animation, int size, int ballSize, int ptValue, int moveAmountX, int moveAmountY, int x, int y, java.awt.Color c)
      Constructs a virus with the instance variables set for a specified size. This constructor is used when an exiting virus on the screen is hit and splits
      Parameters:
      animation - the animation this object is part of
      size - the size (large, medium, small) of the virus
      ballSize - the size in pixels of the virus on the screen
      ptValue - the pt value the virus adds to the score when it is hit
      moveAmountX - the amount the virus moves horizontally each time next frame is called
      moveAmountY - the amount the virus moves vertically each time next frame is called
      x - the x position of the virus's left side
      y - the y position of the virus's top
      c - the color of the virus on the screen

      public void nextFrame()

    • wrapAround

      public void wrapAround()
      Keeps the virus from disappearing off the screen. When the virus hits the edge of the screen if appears on the opposite edge, somewhat offset from where it went off the screen on the other end.

      Makes the virus disappear when it is hit by the doctor

    • split

      public java.util.ArrayList<Virus> split()
      The method creates two smaller viruses when the virus is hit by the doctor. If the current virus is already at the smallest size, the virus will disappear
      Returns:
      ret an arrayList containing the new viruses that the old one splits into returns an empty list if the virus is already at its smallest size
